[ssm/design/legacy-docs-query-cutover] Design source-bound query cutover (notstarted)
The current legacy runtime formats aggregate hits and warnings without the
source/snapshot provenance required by the unified health gate. It is the
pre-activation program outside the source control plane while
ssm/design/legacy-docs-precutover stages the initial source-bound publication;
no control-plane reader delegates to it or wraps its replies.
At one activation boundary, every public query route moves directly to the
master publication and its common health gate. Settle the deployment/routing
boundary and removal of legacy reader behavior so no public route exposes both
models. No public query may return an aggregate bridge reply or mix aggregate
legacy hits with source-bound health validation.
Accept: the owner confirms an atomic point at which current indexed material
moves from the legacy runtime to a fully source-bound publication, and that
after it no legacy aggregate reader, compatibility reply, or unprovenanced hit
