[ssm/design/command-surface] Design the scout command surface (notstarted)
Before any implementation starts, carefully design and encapsulate the two
invocation surfaces: (1) a source proposal command -- validates a complete
ordered batch of immutable-name `add` declarations and target-only `remove`
rows before runtime work, returning every failed row without fetch, intent,
ledger, or publication side effects. Given the settled batch rule, it applies
the accepted plan through corresponding source publication or removal; it never
exposes a declaration change before that publication boundary completes. The
batch reports one outcome per operation and never derives further URLs; (2)
refresh all sources past their TTL -- no argument, scans and re-fetches only
stale/missing entries, applying its own re-fetch results through the same
publication path.
Resolve the public-name/scope mismatch too: either add-source is the public
name for the full batch add/remove proposal command or the public name changes,
so readers never have to infer unavailable operations.
Each command needs its own representation on both the CLI and the MCP tool
surface: exact argument shape, one settled outcome record per input row, and
how both stay isolated from the ledger's internal locking/crash-safety
mechanics in ssm/design/source-registry so those internals can change without
changing either calling contract. Apply the
settled fetch-admission, MIME-representation, and fresh-source-refetch
policies plus the settled batch-atomicity contract: an `add` targeting a fresh
source re-fetches, while refresh-stale remains stale/absent-only. Normal
proposal application is blocked while the current store is invalid; the complete
validation failure report names the repair path. Row outcomes must name the
lifecycle stage reached and carry the settled structured diagnostic when one
exists, not conceal a fetch, representation, ledger, index, or validation
failure as an ordinary success.
Accept: the owner confirms the settled two-command CLI + MCP contract before ssm/implement/add-source and ssm/implement/refresh-stale begin.
